       cc [options] file -lcurses #include <unctrl.h>

       char *unctrl(chtype c);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The function generates a character string that is a print-
       able representation of c.  If c is a control character, it
       is  converted to the ^X notation.  If c contains rendition
       information, the effect is undefined.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluuee
       Upon successful completion, returns the generated  string.
       Otherwise, it returns a null pointer.

EErrrroorrss
       No errors are defined.

